EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to public safety; changing certain traffic violations
from civil infractions to misdemeanors; providing
penalties; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law provides that a violation of any provision of existing law relating
2 to any traffic law or ordinance is a civil infraction unless a criminal penalty is
3 prescribed for the violation by a specific statute. (NRS 481.015) Existing law
4 prohibits certain acts involving driving a vehicle upon a divided highway and
5 provides that such violations are punishable as civil infractions. (NRS 484B.227)
6 This bill makes such violations punishable as misdemeanors.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 484B.227 is hereby amended to read as
2 follows:
3 484B.227 1. Every vehicle driven upon a divided highway
4 must be driven only upon the right-hand roadway and must not be
5 driven over, across or within any dividing space, barrier or section
6 or make any left turn, semicircular turn or U-turn, except through an
7 opening in the barrier or dividing section or space or at a crossover
8 or intersection established by a public authority.
